text: Agdistis arabica is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from Israel, Iran, Pakistan, Bahrain, Saudi Arabia, Yemen, Oman, Somalia, Sudan, Tunisia, Egypt and Pakistan. ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths of the Middle East Category:Fauna of Somalia Category:Moths of the Arabian Peninsula Category:Moths of Western Asia Category:Moths of Africa Category:Moths described in 1958
